            <title>[SHDP-230] Datanode permission for minicluster may fail</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SHDP-230</link>
                <project id="10801" key="SHDP">Spring for Apache Hadoop</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Symptom for older distros is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;08:49:58,087  WARN Test worker datanode.DataNode - Invalid directory in dfs.data.dir: Incorrect permission for build/test/data/HadoopClusterTests/dfs/data/data1, expected: rwxr-xr-x, while actual: rwxrwxr-x&lt;br/&gt;
08:49:58,089  WARN Test worker datanode.DataNode - Invalid directory in dfs.data.dir: Incorrect permission for build/test/data/HadoopClusterTests/dfs/data/data2, expected: rwxr-xr-x, while actual: rwxrwxr-x&lt;br/&gt;
08:49:58,089 ERROR Test worker datanode.DataNode - All directories in dfs.data.dir are invalid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should check what is a real umask and just use that via dfs.datanode.data.dir.perm parameter in Configuration passed into MiniDFSCluster.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
